Package: variogramApp
Type: Package
Title: Shiny Application for Exploring Variograms and Gaussian Random Fields
Version: 0.2.0
Author: Olatunji Johnson [cre, aut] (<https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4080-0999>)
Maintainer: Olatunji Johnson <olatunjijohnson21111@gmail.com>
Description: An interactive Shiny web application for teaching and exploring
    variograms and Gaussian random fields. Users can choose from twelve covariance
    models, adjust parameters (variance, scale, nugget, smoothness), simulate
    Gaussian random fields in one or two dimensions, and compare empirical
    semivariograms against the theoretical curve. Optional Monte Carlo
    permutation envelopes provide a visual significance test for spatial
    correlation.
Imports: geoR, ggplot2, shiny, dplyr
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
URL: https://github.com/olatunjijohnson/variogramApp
BugReports: https://github.com/olatunjijohnson/variogramApp/issues
